Man, I'd forgotten about this site some....not like anyone was listening ot my rants to much XD

Stuff is going going, school is going going. :O I'm Going going CRAAAAZYYYYYYY

Everytime I end up watching these types of documentaries, the smaller I feel and the more scared I become....


I fear the worlds going somewhere dark...

We have moved him in all the way....though we're still moving within a month or two....

*grooves to music before leaving for work*

I dunno, I used to try the whole 'writing out your thoughts of the moment' a few years back to try and sort out my thoughts....but I was depressed at the time, what could I really do?

No, no, I'm not depressed now! Far from it! Well, I hope anyways. I'm just trying to figure out if going back to school next year is the right thing for me to do really. I mean, as fun as being able to go places and do things I couldn't normally do while at school (which Its not as easy as I initially thought), I won't really be getting an education to better my life. I'm just wondering if Genetics is whats right for me. I tried doing the pre-med program here in town, and due to Calculus failing horribly, I'm not sure if it was the best idea for me. Hell, I might have to start off with taking my courses set up so that I can take them 2 at a time or something while still trying to work in a balance between full-time and part-time (I don't really wanna have to move back home, that was stressful enough, not that I love my dear parents, they're just crazy-stressful when I'm trying to do stuff for ME and they butt in..... mother more so than father)


Anyways, that aside, the only things other than that I have to worry about is moving out (which I'm going down to the office today when I get home to check if there are any availabilities for this month) and also getting enough OT down so that I can get my debts obliterated in time for FC (well, in time to save up money for it)

Kinda hard to believe I haven't updated this thing in over a year! ...Plus I should really change that picture, I don't remember being purple O..o;;

Anywhos, I'm at work currently, out in a little box and waiting for the last 2 hours of my shift to dissapear. I kinda wish I was staying home for halloween, but there isn't much I can do about that....

Welllll, lots have changed since my last entry here. I've moved out of my Parent's home, moved in with an awesome room-mate, ze Pagan Foxcat of awesomesauce, worked semi-hard at my job, had landlord fuckerys, obtained a new room-mate, Kyteriah (The OTHER katdragon) of coolness, and now have to move to another appartment due to previously aformentioned landlord fuckery. 


Halloween this year will be kinda teh suck. I can't really dress up at work (Again! I was working LAST year too!)

There's much to be done in recent weeks to come, like work as much OT as possible so that I can climb out of the finanical rut I've been in since FC (and should have long since crawled out of) And get my freedom to go to THIS years FC and still have the finances to move


And now.....I shall vegetate and groove to music for the next hour and a half...

get back to doing a few old things I liked to do, like play on my Alliance characters on WoW (I started there, and it seems, to me, a waist to let them go unused now that I'm sorta horde biased...TAUREN!), get back to playing Piano, and ...uh...um...>_> Being ACTIVE


That is all...I think...

Do you think that I will die a virgin? some people do

If no, will I die spouce-less?

What....the....fuck!??!


D:< Seriously, am I that bad a person? Do I hog people's attention? Do I go out of my way to annoy people? Do I destroy things with reckless abandon? Do I force people to do things against her will? Do I kill puppies? Do I never act mature? (Yes, I know I have my moments, but seriously think about that...), Am I illogical, irrational, dangerous? Am I a rapist? Am I a coked-up criminal that tags buildings and busts peoples windows? Am I a voratious killing machine? Am I a destroyer of lives, killer of familes, anihilator of worlds?


Right now, my life is so routine I've come to see that it's grown rather dull...I mean, I haven't really seen anyone due to the fact that other people are in school/college and stuffs. How is it that I seem to be seemingly destroying relationships? Or even relationships that aren't really very...uh....relationshippy? How is it that I've seemingly become so evil...sitting on my ass doing absolutely nothing half the time, and running around doing stuff for my family....is there an evil clone running around of me? Seriuosly people, quit spouting off terminal logical inexactitudes about my life and we can get back to our happy cohesion of happyness....thank you, one and all


Oh, and to those who think I've become somehow a deliberate evil-annoying-dickhead....I think I found your brain, its hiding here with me. It say your sheer denial of logic and just ranting about untruths about people has scarred it quite muchly....


MiniMike

Finally, after 8 (well, technically 7, but I was sick that day) days of Yee-haw boring-ness, its coming to an end. Finally, I'll be able to reassert some sanity into my body over the next few days

Thank you all!


Ok, on that note, 3 friends and I want to go to Edmonton for a few days, y'know, before they all have to go back to school/college/work kinda thing. We're all for it....however....

The 'rents are deadset against having 4 people (including me) in the car. They're fine with 2, and 3 is pushing it apparently, but 4 is bad. Why you ask? They're first excuse was "We know what kids were like when we were young, and having 3 guys and a girl on a trip like that spells trouble" 

When I assured them that we weren't about to do things like that, and how I had already had assurances from my friends that any horseshit and I would turn the boat around and sail right back on to Fort McMurray (well, drive back, but you get the picture). Then, because I started to get mad and force the issue (Like I always dumbly do) they started to change their reasoning for not letting me go from numbers-in-the-car to its-because-of-the-way-you're-acting. Granted, I can loose my cool with them in these types of situations. But Come OOOOOON! My friends and I aren't that stupid, and if my parents can't trust me worth a sac of wet paper bags.....

Serioulsy, its agrivating, I have three quarters of a mind just to drive on down to Edmonton anyways, with all 4 people aboard, JUST to show the 'rents that 
a) I'm fucking 19
b) I'm not fucking 10
c) That I can go on a small, simple vacation, and not have some sort of disaster 



Whew, ok, now that thats over with, how goes with you guys?



MiniMike

I FOUND THE JACKET!

That is all...



P.S. Feel free to ask what the fuck my post means ^^

1) Excuse to get out of Fort McDump
2) Much purchasing of Manga and the like
3) Making friends and seeing old ones
4) Broadening the realm of Anime-knowledge in my mind...or something
5) Excuse to act like a total retard at times, and get away with it!

Ok, Monday is today, well, it has been for more than half of it already (Thank the powers that be). Today is the day before the day of last-work-day-ness. Which is good. I'm thankful as all hell that there's a computer out here, not only to do this, but to communicate with people. As much as I love reading, I'd like the oppertunity to talk to people more.

FA apparently doesn't like me, or at least it doesn't like my computer....or art....or both. I tried uploading pictures yesterday, and it was, basically, reluctant to show up. I was kinda upset, because I drew a lot yesterday....a lot for me anyways. But FA didn't want it yesteday. I'll have to try again when I get home

And I shall hopefully have moneys by Friday! YAY MONEY!

...

Animethon approaches. I'm going "SQUEE!" inside, but what to go as? My fursuit won't be done, nor do I have my jacket, much less have it embroidered....*Sigh* IDEAS!

One would think having a job that you get to sit on your ass for 12 hours, and get payed 20 bucks for each said hour, would make me feel happy. Well it does, but sometimes dealing with the boredom that insues is unreal. Its not even the begining of my shift and already I'm going "H'OMG SPASM IN BRAIN!" just to keep myself awake....help meeeee!

Poke me on AIM or MSN or anything! Call me even!

Holy hell, can I be more of a dickwad?

This morning started out all right. I woke up early (partially to reset my slowy-becoming-nocturnal sleep habit), dropped my Sis off at school, went downtown, made an appointment to meet with my academic advisor at Keyano, left there, got some breakfast, got my Slann Mage-priest from Kottage toys, went home....Mother was leaving for works soon, and I asked for her to unlock the door to the computer room....this is where I snapped. She refused. At first it was a me-being-selfish moment and demanding she open it....doing the whole childish taking-her-keys ransom thing...then, I realized. To stop myself from doing these things, I had to leave...I know I have to eventually, but recently life at home just seems...unwelcome. Unwelcome just radiates from every crack in the house, even though my parents vehemently deny that they don't want me here. I know I slack off in chores, I'm trying to get better at it....I think the only way I'm going to learn is moving out and having to do this stuff on my own. Today's episode was, by far, not the way to go. I wasted 25 bucks on a cab ride, and my Mom came to get me after I cancelled my bus ticket...

Seriously, what the fuck is wrong with me? Normal people don't go all "HULK SMASH" at a random annoying inncident. Do I just have rage issues or something? Or do I just seriously need to get the fuck out of this town?.....

Someone, please just help me.....

I think its about time I did it anyways, if not just for the summer. I think I need to do something like this, get my life to mean a bit more than just living at home, working. Perhaps once I experience life living away from home I'll learn to apreciate home just a little bit more. This just might be what I need to get back into the "I'm going to school for me" mood, either going back to keyano or going to a different institute. Who knows what'll happen till I do, but I believe I have to step forward and do this for myself, even if it turns out to be a horrific episode or turns out to be a terrific success, I shall do this. 
MiniMike
P.S. Any helpful donations of money or advice would be greatly aprecialted. My parents would probably help, but I'd like to have a little help just in case.

So, yeah, a friend I haven't talked to in a few months due to loosing emails and whatnot , was talking to me today, we exchanged livejournals, then he questioned why I had 2, cause I mentioned that I had two, then there was the guessing as to who it was, and through me dropping oh-so-subtle hints and him investigating, he found this LJ. :D My friends just find out about my furry and vore sides of me in the oddest ways....

Ok, two possibilities here folks, as far as I can see

Number one: I drop English and Stats, and finish the year with Astronomy and Biology, and kick ass at them while I'm at it, and pass them good and done-like. Then, after that, either make sure I can get a decent wage at Superstore working full time, or Work somewhere else working full time at a decent wage, earn enough to either get a car or a new computer (I want the car, so I can travel this summer to see friends.....) and then do whatever it takes to rekindle my motivation towards self-betterment and finding what I wanna do in life....then start school again in Sept 2007.

OR


Number Two: (the one I don't like, btw). Drop everything now, take the 6 months or so to work and get my act together, and then go back to School this fall.....


I know number two isn't very elaborately explained....its cause its not very elaborate....


Comments, suggestions, critisisms? Please, send them my way....

Well, I got a WoW Game card behind my parents backs...now lets just see how long it takes them to catch me, ya? Well, at any rate, anyone wanting to play with me just give me a poke online, I'd be more than happy to come play with ya :3

I also got a new iPod (Horray!), though I'm sorta turning it into an iPorn....I mean, all my vore and yiff pics on there and all that, now I don't have to worry about not being near a computer on a trip, I got enough there to keep me going...well, for a long time.... *evil snicker*

But iPorn aside, I really like how I'm converting all my movies I have and show episodes so that I can watch them on my iPod ^^ *Sqee!* I already have Advent Children and the pilot eps. of SG: Atlantis on there already, so we'll see how much I manage to convert at home, I know my Pod won't have room for it all at once, so I'll just have to pick a few eps. on the go.



Cheers


MiniMike

Just thought I'd put this one out there....

Well, today I went to a party to celebrate my Great Aunt's 100th birthday (even though _Technically_ she isn't 100 till Sunday AKA Tommorow). I saw quite a few people that, even though related, I have such a vauge recolection of. Needless to say, I had a great time talking to all the people there, catching up on things (even if a few of the people I talked to didn't hear half the things I said to them). I was quite amazed at how many people seem to see such awesome potential in me. Apparently my ambitions in things like videography aren't so farfetched a dream as I thought (Which is why I may consider taking such courses at the U of Calgary....maybe, we shall see in the coming year). At any rate, we ate, were merry (and slightly drunk, in my case, had a few glasses of champaign I's did) , and celebrated my Great Aunt's life so far with much zeal. I even, to my parents initial horror, stood up to say a few words. According to them I have a history of doing something stupid when infront of a crowd like that, but I much pleased them when all I did was say a few thoughtful and artisticly chosen words. Needless to say, they now think me a bit more mature than the son that used to just go up there and do something incredibly goofy in a "Look at me" fasion.... 




Anyways, I'm off to do some other things. Hope everyone is well

MiniMike



P.S. Its hard to disguise arousement when your cousins dog is gnawing and slobbering on your arm ;_;

Yup, yup it has been a while. Though I'm not to sure what's so interesting in my life as current to warrent a LJ post, here goes

For Starters, The semester is ok, but I need to get people, several in fact, to poke me every once in a while to make me read my English readings, or see if I can get my Stats assignment done. Seriously, this semester isn't all that heavy, I should be able to pass with flying colors. 

Tommorow I'm going hunting for a Movie or Tape cassete or something of The Tempest...so then I can follow it easyer, and be able to knwo whats going on.


And talk to me, people, seriously, I don't bite! .....often....I nibble!


MiniMike


P.S. Blarg, sick

I didn't sleep very well....
WoW is down
I wanna sleep, but cant...

;_; I R Teh Sad


Anyways..... X-mas is coming, and I can only get gifts to my immediate family..... Sorry friends, you're going to have to wait....and it will probably be some shitty 10 buck thing....but at least I care!

'm dropping my 2 chemistry courses and Calculus this semester...why? Because there's no hope in hell to pass them at this point. I feel, and I have parental (at least one of them) support on this too to drop them, and finish Bio and English.... I'm probably going to take some other courses next semester besides the chem ones, ....well, only 1 other course, and take the other Bio course.....and continue english....so only three courses next semester....yays! 

This is just something to keep me occupied, I guess, so that I'm at least learning something....my parents feel as long as I'm going to school, its all good. Now I can also earn some more money on the side. So...yeah....well, if anyone wants to call me, please do, I'm a bit lonely.... 'course those who usually call me on weekends or for weekends need not apply, buecause you's will call anyways..I hope XD

So, school is good. and I think the course line up will be English (for I can't drop it) , Bio 108 and Astronomy... sounds good to me!


MiniMike

At first I thought, and really did hope, that her display name was just a joke, but apparently Stephanie, whom I met last year at animethon, died on the 23rd....how or why I don't know yet....but this comes at probably the worst time of year for me....college is going down the shitter, and now this.....I'm really, truely lost now...

I got yelled at today for another stupid thing! Guess what I did this time folks! Close the fridge 100% of the way, then get blamed for when something falls after I leave the room and knocks is open! Yup, I just looove psycicly not knowing when things are going to happen outside of my control.... Also, I know I failed my Chem lab final And Also, I know, I will probably pass just barely in most of my courses this semester, Calculus in itself will be a miricle And Also Also, I know, that I can't have the friends I had through high school all my life, but doing dirty, underhanded tricks or just ignoring me is a hurtful way to go.... I mean, drifting away when neither party contacts is another, but ignoring you?............No attempt at communication; its like I'm not even there..... I mean, just because I either go to a different school now, or am not calling 24/7, doesn't mean I don't exsist..... I notice that, while in past years I was sorta semi-asked to birthday parties, I only got 1 this year out of the 3 I knew happened within the last month and a half..... so, yeah, not wanted by them anymore *******EDIT********

So...yeah...blah....

I feel like I don't want to be in college...or, actually a better description would be that I don't feel like I belong in college this year, that I should have taken a year off and just saved money (And possibly a bit for a car and a roadtrip or two....or three) *sigh* feedback? Thoughts? Suggestions? I sure need them....

:3 Yeeehaw, only one more midterm to endure!

Ok...I seriously can't wait to get the frick outa school. Its caused me enough stress as it is. And then, believed or not folks, My Mom started yelling at me last night about my marks, as if I wasn't depressed for a majority of the semester. I seriously tried the best I could considering, and she's all like, Doom-and-gloom-you-failed-at-life .....yeah, great vote o' confidance there Mom > . >

Well, on the upside, I'm almost done my scrapbook, almost done the classes (its just review now), and I have 1 and 1/2 exams this week....blarg, I seriously need to see the Math teachers soon for review...and start talking to Drew about Math and Social review......like holy frig!

Chemistry and Physics I'm less worried about, though I still am.

....Oh lovely, just took a peak outside the library window, and its pooring again... hehe, that reminds me, I need to learn how to cast fire spells so I can dry out my friend in Calgary...hehe

Not much else I can put, 'cept for the small fact that I got into another accident (Toootally not my fault...) I got rear ended by some lady who thought I was going through the yellow light....which was yellow for a bout a second > . >....genious lady

So yeah, Animethon = look for alternative transportation


--Mecha

OMGWTFSQUEE! Apple got my iPod yesterday, and sent me a convenient automated e-mail to tell me so. Now that I know its there, I can wait with peace of mind......well, for a while at least

OMGWTFSTRESS!!! > . < School = Death. Seriously, I'm going to go cwazy by the end of my last test and, hopefully, can still go to Animethon depending on the outcome of these tests. Also, hopefully, I can have a social life (I had one? :| ) at the end of exams again. This year, it seams, whenever I tried to have fun with my friends while balancing school, something happened to throw it all arse over tea kettle.
